, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"about 1210–June 1327":"circa 1210–juni 1327","1210–1327":"1210–1327","–Female":"Overleden","1230–1336":"1230–1336","1190–1327":"1190–1327","1190":"1190","1327":"1327","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1336":"1336","1224":"1224","June 1327":"juni 1327","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","about 1210":"circa 1210","about 1230":"circa 1230","Stapleford, Leicestershire, England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, England","Scaldford, Leicestershire,England":"Leicestershire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"about 1210–June 1327":"about 1210–June 1327","1210–1327":"1210–1327","–Female":"Deceased","1230–1336":"1230–1336","1190–1327":"1190–1327","1190":"1190","1327":"1327","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1336":"1336","1224":"1224","June 1327":"June 1327","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","about 1210":"about 1210","about 1230":"about 1230","Stapleford, Leicestershire, England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, England","Scaldford, Leicestershire,England":"Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hauberk","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Hubert  .","French: from the personal name <i>Aubert</i>, a late medieval form of an ancient Germanic compound name, <i>Adalberht</i> (see   Albert  ).","French: perhaps a metonymic occupational name for someone who made or wore a mailcoat, French <i>haubert</i>, from Old French <i>halberc</i>, <i>hauberc</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Hubert","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Lucien, Armand, Normand, Olivier, Adlore, Alphonse, Andre, Benoit, Camil, Camille, Fernand.","German, Dutch, English, French, Walloon, Breton, Polish, Czech, Slovak, and Jewish (Ashkenazic): from a personal name composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>hug</i> ‘heart, mind, spirit’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’. The name was borne by an 8th-century Christian saint, bishop of Maastricht, who was adopted as the patron of hunters, and helped to increase the popularity of the personal name, especially in the Low Countries.","History: Jean-François-Barthélemi Hubert from Granville in Manche, France, married Félicité Arsenault in Havre-Aubert, QC, in 1801. Nicolas Hubert <i>dit</i> Lacroix from France married Marguerite Landreau in France <i>c.</i> 1653, died in Montreal, QC, in 1687. René Hubert from Paris, France, married Françoise (de) Lacroix in Quebec City, QC, in 1669. Pierre-Paul Hébert/Hubert from France married Suzanne Laporte in QC <i>c.</i> 1716. — This surname is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of South Carolina."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":5,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":14,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":49,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William Hauberk II Lord of Stapleford was born about 1210, in Stapleford, Leicestershire, England as the son of Robert Hauberk I Lord of Scaldford and Unknown. He had at least 1 son with Unknown. He died in June 1327, at the age of 118."},"et":{"about 1210–June 1327":"umbes 1210–juuni 1327","1210–1327":"1210–1327","–Female":"Surnud","1230–1336":"1230–1336","1190–1327":"1190–1327","1190":"1190","1327":"1327","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1336":"1336","1224":"1224","June 1327":"juuni 1327","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","about 1210":"umbes 1210","about 1230":"umbes 1230","Stapleford, Leicestershire, England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, England","Scaldford, Leicestershire,England":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1210–June 1327":"noin 1210–kesäkuu 1327","1210–1327":"1210–1327","–Female":"Kuollut","1230–1336":"1230–1336","1190–1327":"1190–1327","1190":"1190","1327":"1327","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1336":"1336","1224":"1224","June 1327":"kesäkuu 1327","1210":"1210","1230":"1230","about 1210":"noin 1210","about 1230":"noin 1230","Stapleford, Leicestershire, England":"Stapleford, Leicestershire, England","Scaldford, Leicestershire,England":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1210–June 1327":"environ 1210–juin 1327","1210–1327":"12